# Description
***
Thul Kuldor is a dwarven stronghold nestled within the heart of the mountain that shares its name. Carved deep into the rugged terrain, the entrance to Thul Kuldor stands as a formidable structure, reminiscent of a cathedral, both imposing and majestic. Within its depths lie a sprawling network of shafts, tunnels, halls, chambers, and natural caverns, forming a bustling community where the clang of hammers and the echoes of dwarven voices reverberate through the stone.

# Geography
***
Surrounded by rocky terrain and towering peaks, Thul Kuldor is enveloped by the towering mass of the mountain that shelters it. Wrapped by the mountain's contours, creating an easily defensible hollow, Thul Kuldor is an extremely fortifiable stronghold. The rugged landscape not only provides natural defenses but also serves as an example of the Dwarven culture of settling within the largest peaks within a region.

# Government
***
Thul Kuldor is governed by a self-proclaimed monarchy, a system that emerges during times of crisis when decisive leadership is needed. King Dulgrun Silverbeard, the current ruler, ascended to power during a conflict with a colony of Myconids, known as the Mycellium Encroachment, earning the loyalty of his subjects through his steadfast leadership, unwavering determination, and prowess in battle. Succession is typically hereditary until challenged, relying on the monarch's effectiveness and the approval of the populace.

# History
***
Legend holds that Thul Kuldor was established by dwarves who were sent to the Bygone Valley by Khazadune himself, the Architect of Mountains. Tasked with a divine mission, these dwarves carved their stronghold deep into the heart of Thul Kuldor, forging a bastion of dwarven culture and faith, as they were created to do.

Over the centuries, Thul Kuldor flourished, its halls echoing with the sounds of hammer and anvil as dwarven craftsmen honed their skills and forged great works of stonework and metallurgy.

Nearly 150 years ago, during the Mycelium Encroachment, Thul Kuldor faced its greatest challenge as a massive colony of Myconids threatened the security of the dwarven stronghold. Led by King Dulgrun Silverbeard, the dwarves rallied to defend their home against the fungal invaders in a war that tested their resilience and determination.

# Inhabitants
***
The denizens of Thul Kuldor are a proud and industrious people, embodying the steadfast spirit of the dwarven race. Craftsmen, warriors, scholars, and miners work tirelessly within the mountain's embrace, their lives intertwined with the stone and metal of their surroundings. Despite the challenges they face, the dwarves of Thul Kuldor remain resolute, drawing strength from their deep-seated faith in Khazadune, the Architect of Mountains, who they believe watches over them from within the depths of the mountain.
